SUMMARY:Seattle Intro to AI Development Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to build your first AI web application at the University of Washington – Beginner friendly\, no experience required. \nJoin us for our Intro to AI Development Workshop\, a full-day\, hands-on program where you’ll build your first AI web application and learn the fundamentals of creating your own AI apps. \nNo coding experience is required. Every participant will receive free API key credits to experiment with leading models such as GPT\, Claude\, Gemini\, and more. \nBy the end of the workshop\, you will have built a custom Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) chatbot. You’ll upload your own dataset\, prompt the chatbot to generate outputs\, and see how industry-standard GenAI models can be integrated into practical applications. This project-based approach gives you a clear starting point to extend your skills into more advanced AI development. \nThe day concludes with a showcase where participants can demo their projects\, connect with peers\, and ask questions directly to the instructors from Circuit Stream. \nWe look forward to seeing what you create! \nEvent Instructor: Guillaume Duteaud \nWhat You’ll Learn:\n– How to use Python to interact with leading AI models like OpenAI’s GPT\, Anthropic’s Claude\, Google Gemini\, Meta’s Llama\, and more\n– How to upload documents and connect them to an AI assistant using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)\n– How to prompt\, test\, and refine your assistant to answer questions accurately using your own data\n– How modern web apps integrate AI features—from concept to deployment \nWhat’s Included:\n– A full day of hands-on training in AI development using Python and real industry tools\n– A working AI assistant that you build using your own dataset\, and can continue to expand after the workshop\n– Free API credits to experiment with tools like GPT\, Claude\, Gemini\, and Llama\n– A project template and resource bundle to support your next steps after the workshop\n– A chance to meet instructors\, developers\, and other aspiring AI builders during the workshop showcase\n– A catered lunch \nWho Should Attend:\nThis workshop is designed for aspiring AI developers\, career changers\, and curious professionals who want to start building with AI. Whether you’re exploring a new career path\, working on a side project\, or looking to bring AI tools into your current role\, you’ll leave with a working project and a clear path forward. \nWhat to Bring:\n– A laptop (Mac or Windows)\n– We’ll provide step-by-step instructions before the workshop to help you set up your environment. If you’re new to Python\, we’ll also send you an optional pre-work tutorial to help you feel confident before arriving.\n– We’ll supply all necessary tools\, a project template\, and free API credits sponsored by Circuit Stream. \nSpaces are limited to keep the experience personal and hands-on. Whether you’re exploring AI for the first time or building on past experience\, this workshop gives you a clear starting point and a working project you can keep improving. Reserve your seat now!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/seattle-intro-to-ai-development-workshop/
LOCATION:Maple Hall Great Room\, Maple Hall\, University of Washington\, Maple Hall Great Room\, Maple Hall\, University of Washington\, Seattle\, 98105\, United States
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence,Science
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Seattle-6.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Circuit Stream":MAILTO:rio@circuitstream.com
END:VEVENT
