SUMMARY:Rooted & Rising: Powering Climate Tech for the Next Generation
DESCRIPTION:The Collective Seattle — Alpenglow Room\n​Join VertueLab this Earth Day for an evening with curious minds\, bold builders\, and community champions\, exploring what becomes possible when climate innovation meets collective action. What must we build today to ensure the next generation inherits a thriving climate innovation ecosystem? \n​This interactive and engaging gathering brings together civic\, academic\, philanthropic\, and business leaders to reimagine the future we are creating in the Pacific Northwest. Through inspiring stories from climate tech founders and cross-generational conversations together\, we will explore how the region can become a national leader in climate technology and build an equitable climate future that will benefit generations to come. The best conversations happen across generations: if you’re older than 30\, consider bringing a guest who’s younger than thirty\, and vice versa! \n​In the spirit of Earth Day and climate stewardship\, we encourage guests to use public transportation\, bike\, or walk when possible. The venue is easily accessible by multiple bus routes and light rail connections. \n​Thank you to our event sponsors: Beneficial State Bank\, Kern and Thompson\, Community Energy Labs\, and TrainSnap Inc.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/rooted-rising-powering-climate-tech-for-the-next-generation/
LOCATION:The Collective\, 400 Dexter Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Screenshot-2026-04-10-131725.png
GEO:47.6221728;-122.3419734
