SUMMARY:Seattle SOLIDWORKS User Group: Celebrating 30 Years of Innovation
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the 30th anniversary celebration of the Seattle Area SOLIDWORKS Power Users Group\, the first SOLIDWORKS User Group! This milestone event is not just a celebration of three decades of shared knowledge\, but also a chance for you to connect with fellow SOLIDWORKS enthusiasts\, share experiences\, and be inspired by the innovations that have shaped our journey. Whether you’re a veteran user\, launching a new startup\, or new to the world of SOLIDWORKS\, this is an opportunity to discover new ideas and rekindle your passion. \nThis is the very first SOLIDWORKS User Group to hit 30 years and we are so excited to celebrate with the entire community. \nThis event is totally free and will also be livestreamed on Zoom. \nWhat to Expect\n🎉 Celebrate 30 Years of Community — honoring the world’s first SOLIDWORKS User Group and the people who built it \n💡 Inspiring Technical Sessions — real-world tips\, workflows\, and insights you can immediately apply \n🗨️ Exclusive Panel Discussion with Tech Executives – Suchit Jain (VP Strategy & Business Dev SOLIDWORKS) & Vineet Thuvara (Chief Product Officer at Fluke Corporation) \n🤝 Unmatched Networking — connect with engineers\, designers\, makers\, startups and industry leaders from across the region \n🚀 Community Energy — meet passionate SOLIDWORKS users who love sharing knowledge and helping each other grow \n🍽️ Food\, Conversations & Celebration — because the best ideas happen between sessions. Coffee\, snacks\, and a full dinner. \n😎 Prizes and Giveaways – SOLIDWORKS SWAG\, software\, gift cards\, and more!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/seattle-solidworks-user-group-celebrating-30-years-of-innovation/
LOCATION:Museum of Flight\, 9404 E. Marginal Way S.\, Seattle\, United States
CATEGORIES:Aerospace,Conferences,Educational events,Meetups
