SUMMARY:Seattle Universal Math Museum's Annual Auction and Fund-a-Need
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a fun way to support the first math museum on the west coast? Get your tickets to Golden Evening for the benefit of SUMM\, a vibrant night in support of the Seattle Universal Math Museum (SUMM). Join a community of educators\, artists\, and supporters who believe math should be creative\, joyful\, and accessible to all. \nWhat to Expect\n– A cocktail party with appetizers and drinks\n– Giving opportunities take place during the Auction and Fund-a-Need portion of the evening\n– A chance to connect with community leaders\, families\, and supporters\n– Light\, math-inspired challenges and interactive moments throughout the reception\n– A special live performance by Allison Henrich\, featuring mathematical rope tricks that tie patterns and problem-solving into beautifully knotty conclusions. \nTickets: $100 per guest
