SUMMARY:Scaling Your AI Partnership: Execution by Design
DESCRIPTION:𝗢𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗲𝘄\nMove beyond prompts to running real projects through AI. Build the containers\, recaps\, and refinement loops that scale your work. \nYou’ve learned how to collaborate with AI. Now it’s time to run real work through it. \nMost professionals hit a ceiling. Individual prompts work fine\, but the moment work gets complex\, things start breaking. Conversations expand and lose focus. Context fades between sessions. Outputs get harder to refine. Work drifts from the original objective without anyone noticing. \n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝘀𝗻’𝘁 𝗮 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗲𝗺. 𝗜𝘁’𝘀 𝗮 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺𝘀 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗲𝗺. \nExecution by Design is a hands-on workshop that installs the operational mechanics behind high-performance AI collaboration. You’ll move from structured conversations to running full projects through AI with clarity\, continuity\, and control. \n𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗬𝗼𝘂’𝗹𝗹 𝗪𝗮𝗹𝗸 𝗔𝘄𝗮𝘆 𝗪𝗶𝘁𝗵 \n· A container architecture that segments complex work so context stays clean and predictable \n· Recap and continuity practices that let work build across sessions instead of resetting every time \n· The ability to detect and correct alignment drift as problems get more complex \n· A structured refinement cycle that turns mediocre AI output into sharp\, usable work \n· A workflow lifecycle approach for managing multiple work streams intentionally \n· A personalized 60-day execution plan tied to a real project you’re working on \n𝗪𝗵𝗼 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗜𝘀 𝗙𝗼𝗿 \nKnowledge workers\, leaders\, consultants\, and professionals who already use AI regularly and want to move beyond prompting toward running complex work through a structured AI partnership. \nThis workshop assumes familiarity with the foundational principles from Workshop 1: Collaboration by Design. \n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗖𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝗜𝗱𝗲𝗮 \nRelational discipline enables collaboration. Execution discipline enables performance. When container architecture\, recap discipline\, and alignment monitoring are installed\, AI becomes capable of supporting complex intellectual work\, not just isolated tasks. \nThis isn’t a tips-and-tricks session. You’ll build the operating system behind your AI partnership.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/scaling-your-ai-partnership-execution-by-design/
LOCATION:The Pioneer Collective – West Canal Yards\, 1100 W Ewing Street\, Seattle\, 98119\, United States
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence
