SUMMARY:Ethics & Tech Conference
DESCRIPTION:Join Seattle University’s Technology Ethics Initiative for the fourth annual Ethics & Tech Conference\, focused this year on technology\, energy and security. As artificial intelligence reshapes global power\, cyber threats grow more sophisticated\, and competition over energy and infrastructure intensifies\, this year’s conference takes on some of the most urgent questions of our time. \nThis year’s keynote speaker is Amandeep Singh Gill\, United Nations Under-Secretary-General and Special Envoy for Digital and Emerging Technologies\, a global leader shaping international policy on artificial intelligence and digital governance. \nFrom AI-driven cybersecurity risks and techno-nationalism to the rising energy demands of data centers and the future of alternative energy systems\, speakers will explore how technology is redefining security\, resilience and global influence. \nJoin us as we consider how responsible innovation can shape a more secure and sustainable future.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/ethics-tech-conference/
LOCATION:Pigott Auditorium\, Seattle University\, 901 12th Avenue\, Seattle\, CA\, 98101\, United States
